@joewitt @apiri 
Some LICENSE and NOTICE changes here.  I tried to pull everything up to the levels needed for things that were bundled in NARs/assemblies from several versions of Groovy used either explicitly or through transitive dependencies.  There might need to be some formatting changes, but this represents everything Groovy-related that I found while doing the upgrade.

Do these changes look correct?  One issue I see is in our current LICENSE files in the assemblies have multiple versions of the same library.  I'd like to make sure the version information is included if it needs to be.  I'm assuming for all versions of a bundled dependency, its specific LICENSE and NOTICE content needs to be accounted for, not just the newest version.

@mattyb149 thanks for the update all looks good

+1

Will squash and merge
